{"id":412113,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/V%C3%A9hicule_Blind%C3%A9_L%C3%A9ger","text":"The V\u00E9hicule Blind\u00E9 L\u00E9ger or VBL (light armoured vehicle) is a four-wheel drive reconnaissance light military vehicle. It has been used by the French army since 1990. More than 25 foreign countries used it, including Gabon, Qatar, and Serbia. The US Army used it as M11 for hazardous material reconnaissance. Russia bought 500 of them in November 2012.\nThe vehicle is designed and built in France by Panhard.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Four-wheel_drive","surface_form":"four-wheel drive","offset":63},{"uri":"Reconnaissance","surface_form":"reconnaissance","offset":80},{"uri":"Military","surface_form":"military","offset":101},{"uri":"Vehicle","surface_form":"vehicle","offset":110},{"uri":"France","surface_form":"French","offset":143},{"uri":"Army","surface_form":"army","offset":150},{"uri":"1990","surface_form":"1990","offset":161},{"uri":"Country","surface_form":"countries","offset":188},{"uri":"Gabon","surface_form":"Gabon","offset":217},{"uri":"Qatar","surface_form":"Qatar","offset":224},{"uri":"Serbia","surface_form":"Serbia","offset":235},{"uri":"US_Army","surface_form":"US Army","offset":247},{"uri":"Hazardous_material","surface_form":"hazardous material","offset":274},{"uri":"Russia","surface_form":"Russia","offset":309},{"uri":"2012","surface_form":"2012","offset":347},{"uri":"France","surface_form":"France","offset":390},{"uri":"Panhard","surface_form":"Panhard","offset":400}]}